CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 10, reads: "Post-Holiday Party - Missionary Group Two of Wesley Center AME Zion Church had a post-holiday party at the residence of Mrs. Martha Franklin, 7640 Susquehanna St., Monday night. Participants, back row, left to right, were Mmes. J. Foster, L. Devereaux, S. Moon, D. Banks, W. Rice, the Rev. and Mrs. C. H. Foggie, M. Franklin, C. Hayes, E. Hawkins and M. Johnson. Seated Mmes. V. White, A. Woodson, I. Glenn, president, L. Washington, A. Moore, R. Parker, L. Williams, K. Bryant, M. Young, and R. Campbell. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Wesley Center AME Zion missionary group including back row: J. Foster, L. Devereaux, S. Moon, D. Banks, Willa Mae Rice, Rev. Charles H. Foggie, Madeline Sharpe Foggie, M. Franklin, C. Hayes, E. Hawkins and Martha Johnson; seated: V. White, A. Woodson, Irene Glenn, L. Washington, A. Moore, R. Parker, L. Williams, K. Bryant, M. Young, and R. Campbell, gathered with wrapped gifts in Franklin home, 7640 Susquehanna Street, another version
